{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:mark.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "mark",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Mark 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Mark 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:1",
      "text": "He entered again into the synagogue, and there was a man there whose hand was withered.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:2",
      "text": "They watched him, whether he would heal him on the Sabbath day, that they might accuse him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:3",
      "text": "He said to the man whose hand was withered, “ Stand up.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:4",
      "text": "He said to them, “ Is it lawful on the Sabbath day to do good or to do harm? To save a life or to kill?” But they were silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:5",
      "text": "When he had looked around at them with anger, being grieved at the hardening of their hearts, he said to the man, “ Stretch out your hand.” He stretched it out, and his hand was restored as healthy as the other.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:6",
      "text": "The Pharisees went out, and immediately conspired with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:7",
      "text": "Jesus withdrew to the sea with his disciples; and a great multitude followed him from Galilee, from Judea,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:8",
      "text": "from Jerusalem, from Idumaea, beyond the Jordan, and those from around Tyre and Sidon. A great multitude, hearing what great things he did, came to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:9",
      "text": "He spoke to his disciples that a little boat should stay near him because of the crowd, so that they wouldn’ t press on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:10",
      "text": "For he had healed many, so that as many as had diseases pressed on him that they might touch him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:11",
      "text": "The unclean spirits, whenever they saw him, fell down before him and cried, “ You are the Son of God!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:12",
      "text": "He sternly warned them that they should not make him known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:13",
      "text": "He went up into the mountain and called to himself those whom he wanted, and they went to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:14",
      "text": "He appointed twelve, that they might be with him, and that he might send them out to preach",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:15",
      "text": "and to have authority to heal sicknesses and to cast out demons:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:16",
      "text": "Simon (to whom he gave the name Peter);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:17",
      "text": "James the son of Zebedee; and John, the brother of James, (whom he called Boanerges, which means, Sons of Thunder);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:18",
      "text": "Andrew; Philip; Bartholomew; Matthew; Thomas; James, the son of Alphaeus; Thaddaeus; Simon the Zealot;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:19",
      "text": "and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed him. Then he came into a house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:20",
      "text": "The multitude came together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:21",
      "text": "When his friends heard it, they went out to seize him; for they said, “ He is insane.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:22",
      "text": "The scribes who came down from Jerusalem said, “ He has Beelzebul,” and, “ By the prince of the demons he casts out the demons.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:23",
      "text": "He summoned them and said to them in parables, “ How can Satan cast out Satan?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:24",
      "text": "If a kingdom is divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:25",
      "text": "If a house is divided against itself, that house cannot stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:26",
      "text": "If Satan has risen up against himself, and is divided, he can ’ t stand, but has an end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:27",
      "text": "But no one can enter into the house of the strong man to plunder unless he first binds the strong man; then he will plunder his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:28",
      "text": "“Most certainly I tell you, all sins of the descendants of man will be forgiven, including their blasphemies with which they may blaspheme;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:29",
      "text": "but whoever may blaspheme against the Holy Spirit never has forgiveness, but is subject to eternal condemnation.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:30",
      "text": "— because they said, “ He has an unclean spirit.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:31",
      "text": "His mother and his brothers came, and standing outside, they sent to him, calling him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:32",
      "text": "A multitude was sitting around him, and they told him, “ Behold, your mother, your brothers, and your sisters are outside looking for you.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:33",
      "text": "He answered them, “ Who are my mother and my brothers?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:34",
      "text": "Looking around at those who sat around him, he said, “ Behold, my mother and my brothers!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:mark.3.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "mark",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Mark 3:35",
      "text": "For whoever does the will of God is my brother, my sister, and mother.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
